This paper deals with resource management in large-scale virtualized data center environments, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses network traffic and cost reduction, which suggests a possible sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) metaheuristic for multi-objective optimization indicates a possible sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the optimization of power consumption, which suggests a possible sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for dynamic VM consolidation, which suggests a possible sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
